license_description: Adobe Photoshop is a raster graphics editor developed and published by Adobe Inc. for Windows and macOS
Adobe Acrobat is a family of application software and Web services to view, create, manipulate, print and manage Portable Document Format (PDF) files
Microsoft Visio is a diagramming and vector graphics application and is part of the Microsoft Office family
MS Office is a family of client software, server software, and services that provides a word processor (Word), spreadsheet program (Excel), presentation program (PowerPoint), email client (Outlook)
VMware Workstation enables users to set up virtual machines (VMs) on a single physical machine and use them simultaneously along with the host machine
Microsoft Teams is a business communication platform developed by Microsoft, that offers workspace chat and videoconferencing, file storage, and application integration features
Microsoft Project is a project management tool, designed to assist a project manager in developing a schedule, assigning resources to tasks, tracking progress, managing budget, analyzing workloads.
SAP GUI is the graphical user interface client in SAP ERP's 3-tier architecture of database, application server and client.
SAP HANA is an in-memory, column-oriented, relational database management system developed and marketed by SAP
McAfee Endpoint Security is an integrated, centrally managed endpoint protection platform, having advanced defenses like machine learning-based analysis and behavioral monitoring.
Oracle Autonomous Database is an all-in-one cloud database solution for data marts, data lakes, operational reporting, and batch data processing.
Microsoft SQL Server is a relational database management system, with the primary function of storing and retrieving data as requested by other software applications
WebSphere Application Server is a software product that performs the role of a web application server. It is a software framework and middleware that hosts Java-based web applications
Oracle WebLogic Server is an application server for building enterprise applications using Java EE standards, and deploying them on a reliable, scalable runtime with low cost of ownership.
Microsoft Visual Studio is an integrated development environment from Microsoft. It is used to develop computer programs, as well as websites, web apps, web services and mobile apps.
